OL,3,CGovernment plans new offence to crack
OL,4,Cdown on promoting Channel crossings
OL,5,Conline
OL,7,FAnyone who advertises Channel
OL,8,Fcrossings or fake passports on social
OL,9,Fmedia could face up to five years in
OL,10,Fprison under new plans.
OL,12,FMinisters are seeking to create a new
OL,13,Foffence under the Border Security,
OL,14,FAsylum and Immigration Bill already
OL,15,Fgoing through parliament, to widen its
OL,16,Fscope to tackle illegal entry to the
OL,17,FUK.
