OL,3,CGovernment plans new offence to crack
OL,4,Cdown on promoting Channel crossings
OL,5,Conline
OL,7,FThe National Crime Agency already
OL,8,Fworks with social media companies to
OL,9,Fremove posts promoting crossings, with
OL,10,Fmore than 8,000 taken offline in 2024.
OL,12,FNCA Director General of Operations Rob
OL,13,FJones said the proposed new offence
OL,14,Fwill give them more options of how to
OL,15,Ftarget gangs and their business models.
OL,17,FPrevious cases that could have been
OL,18,Ftargeted under the proposed offence
OL,19,Finclude a Preston-based smuggler
OL,20,Fjailed for 17 years for posting videos
OL,21,Fof migrants thanking him for his help.
